        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 9 at 5:21PM EDT by NWS Charleston SC</headline>
        <description>At 521 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Bennetts Point, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Johns Island, West Ashley, James Island, Hollywood, Folly Beach,
Ravenel, Seabrook Island, Kiawah Island, Meggett and Rockville.
</description>
        <instruction>Stay tuned to NOAA Weather Radio All Hazards, TV or your local news
source for the latest information from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
